	<section class="section-block" id="about">
		<h2 id="about-heading">About Z100 New York</h2>
		<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Z100 (WHTZ 100.3 FM) is New York City&#8217;s top-rated pop radio station, part of the iHeartMedia network. It runs current hits all day, check the recently played list and you&#8217;ll find Doja Cat, Billie Eilish, and Bruno Mars stacked one after another, which tells you everything you need to know about the format.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The station is probably most recognized for the Elvis Duran and the Morning Show. Duran has been in that slot since 1996, which is a long time to keep a morning audience. Ryan Seacrest hosts afternoons. The station also does artist interviews, live events, and the usual concert ticket giveaways. It&#8217;s available at 100.3 FM in New York or via the iHeartRadio app if you&#8217;re listening from anywhere else.</p>
